***(Rewritten-needs final edit)***

Because depression isn't always overt sadness or low mood sometimes it can impact us without much notice. I think of the Latin, *deprimere* which means, "to press down". A literal thumbprint depression into the earth's soil sometimes is a better word picture for "depression" than "feelings of sadness". Persistent numbness, emptiness, low energy and motivation can also be signs of clinical depression.

## What's actually going on

Christian counselors recognize that human beings are complex creations made up of physical bodies and inner spiritual lives. Depression can stem from any combination of these areas: [[1](https://biblicalcounselingcenter.org/depression-is-it-all-in-your-mind/)]

- **The Body (Biology):** Counselors acknowledge that physical factors—such as chemical imbalances, DNA triggers, exhaustion, or illness—can severely impact mood. `<Quote>“Depression is a disorder that alters perception and is not simply a glum mood or a lack of faith.”`, as noted by [**Church and Mental Health**](https://churchandmentalhealth.com/can-christians-take-medication-for-mental-health/). Physical care, including medical treatment, is often supported as a wise gift from God. [[1](https://seattlechristiancounseling.com/articles/a-christian-counselors-perspective-on-depression), [2](https://www.ccef.org/hope-depressed/), [3](https://bellevuechristiancounseling.com/articles/treatment-depression-method-works), [4](https://biblicalcounselingcenter.org/depression-is-it-all-in-your-mind/), [5](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JJwTApxbjNc&t=11)]
- **The Mind (Psychological):** Cognitive elements like destructive thought patterns, unaddressed trauma, grief, or chronic stress are evaluated. Counselors frequently use clinical tools like Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) to help clients challenge feelings of worthlessness. [[1](https://seattlechristiancounseling.com/articles/a-christian-counselors-perspective-on-depression), [2](https://gracechristiancounseling.com/biblical-counseling-for-depression/), [3](https://www.rogerdlin.com/post/how-biblical-counseling-addresses-depression), [4](https://gracechristiancounseling.com/faith-based-therapy-for-overcoming-depression/)]
- **The Soul (Spiritual):** Depression is frequently viewed as the weight of living in a fallen, broken world. It can also be tied to spiritual battles, feelings of separation from God, guilt, or the "dark night of the sou

## How counseling helps

We start by taking honest inventory — what's dimmed, when it dimmed, and what the weight is actually made of. Often there's unprocessed material underneath: grief that never got its turn, anger swallowed for years, a story that says your worth is your output. We work through that at the root, not just at the symptom level.

And we do it within a bigger story. The Christian faith has never pretended the valley doesn't exist — it says the valley is real *and* it isn't the end of the road. Hope, in this office, isn't a greeting-card word. It's the working assumption.

## When to reach out

If you've been flat, checked out, or running on fumes for more than a few weeks — or if the people around you have started asking what's wrong — it's time. If you're having thoughts of ending your life, don't wait for an appointment: call or text 988 now.
